articles.title: NCAA champ Rose Zhang wins LPGA's Mizuho Americas Open in pro debut - ESPN - ESPN
articles.description: Two-time NCAA champion Rose Zhang became the first player in 72 years to win on the LPGA Tour in her pro debut, capturing the Mizuho Americas Open with a par on the second playoff hole against Jennifer Kupcho on Sunday.
articles.content:
JERSEY CITY, N.J. -- Rose Zhang lived up to all the pretournament hype as the next great women's golfer -- at least in her first week as a pro.
